The problem is you're hearing God's word,

00:12:53.780 --> 00:12:57.340
but you're choosing not to do God's word.

00:12:57.340 --> 00:13:00.220
And so the instruction that James follows up with here

00:13:00.220 --> 00:13:02.580
in this passage of scripture at the very beginning

00:13:02.580 --> 00:13:04.340
of his letter or not very far into it,

00:13:04.340 --> 00:13:08.340
he says this, be a doer of the word and not just a hearer.

00:13:08.340 --> 00:13:10.580
James is gonna come back to this idea

00:13:10.580 --> 00:13:13.460
in James chapter four and verse 17 when he says this,

00:13:13.460 --> 00:13:16.740
therefore to him that knoweth to do good.

00:13:16.740 --> 00:13:17.660
How do you know it's good?

00:13:17.660 --> 00:13:19.620
Well, you heard it at some point in time.

00:13:19.640 --> 00:13:21.040
You've seen it in God's word.

00:13:21.040 --> 00:13:22.800
God has shared with you what the good

00:13:22.800 --> 00:13:24.120
or the right thing is to do.

00:13:24.120 --> 00:13:27.800
Therefore to him that knoweth to do good

00:13:27.800 --> 00:13:32.800
and doeth it not, to him it is sin.

00:13:34.320 --> 00:13:37.200
This is where the mirror begins to point out some things

00:13:37.200 --> 00:13:38.960
in our lives that we don't like to hear

00:13:38.960 --> 00:13:41.560
and we start getting angry at the mirror.

00:13:41.560 --> 00:13:44.240
Have you ever stepped in front of the mirror

00:13:44.240 --> 00:13:46.720
and you didn't like what you saw?

00:13:46.740 --> 00:13:50.300
Hair out of place, maybe some drool from the morning,

00:13:50.300 --> 00:13:51.860
maybe you brushed your teeth and you didn't know,

00:13:51.860 --> 00:13:53.540
you know, you had a little bit on the side of your face

00:13:53.540 --> 00:13:55.380
and so your spouse points it out to you

00:13:55.380 --> 00:13:57.420
or maybe, you know, a kid points it out to you

00:13:57.420 --> 00:13:59.580
or something but you come before the mirror

00:13:59.580 --> 00:14:02.660
and you see something there that you don't like.

00:14:02.660 --> 00:14:05.460
Do you punch the mirror every time that happens?

00:14:05.460 --> 00:14:06.980
Probably not.

00:14:06.980 --> 00:14:08.860
If you do, you have a pretty expensive

00:14:08.860 --> 00:14:10.060
mirror budget somewhere.

00:14:11.820 --> 00:14:13.020
What do we do?

00:14:13.020 --> 00:14:15.980
We take what the mirror reveals about us

00:14:16.000 --> 00:14:19.200
and if we don't like it, we probably change

00:14:19.200 --> 00:14:20.320
something about it.

00:14:20.320 --> 00:14:23.119
We go and we wash it off, we comb our hair,

00:14:23.119 --> 00:14:24.740
we do these things, why?

00:14:24.740 --> 00:14:27.320
Because what the mirror reveals to us

00:14:27.320 --> 00:14:30.399
isn't what we want to see.

00:14:31.279 --> 00:14:33.559
Someone who's gonna be a doer of the word

00:14:33.559 --> 00:14:37.679
is someone who has a desire to come before the mirror

00:14:37.679 --> 00:14:41.040
of God's word and say, God, I want you to show me

00:14:41.040 --> 00:14:42.800
truth from your word.

00:14:42.800 --> 00:14:45.600
And so our purpose, when we come before God's word

00:14:46.179 --> 00:14:48.460
is to hear it and it ought to be that we would

00:14:48.460 --> 00:14:53.220
just not hear it but that we would be a doer of the word.

00:14:53.220 --> 00:14:56.380
And so the instruction here really can't get any clearer.

00:14:56.380 --> 00:14:58.899
Do what God's word says.

00:14:58.899 --> 00:15:00.700
That then ought to cause us to step back

00:15:00.700 --> 00:15:05.179
and ask this question, am I doing what God's word says?

00:15:05.179 --> 00:15:08.820
Am I someone who is a hearer of the word

00:15:08.820 --> 00:15:10.899
but not a doer of the word?

00:15:10.899 --> 00:15:12.640
Perhaps we ought to ask it this way,

00:15:12.640 --> 00:15:17.640
in what area of my life am I not doing God's word

00:15:17.980 --> 00:15:19.740
and the truth that I've heard

00:15:19.740 --> 00:15:22.279
or I know I ought to be doing in God's word?

00:15:23.300 --> 00:15:25.660
And so as we come to this passage of scripture,

00:15:25.660 --> 00:15:28.559
James says and uses the illustration of a mirror,

00:15:28.559 --> 00:15:30.140
we're gonna get to that here in just a minute,

00:15:30.140 --> 00:15:33.500
but he says, before we ever address that illustration,

00:15:33.500 --> 00:15:35.420
you need to know God's expectation is this,

00:15:35.420 --> 00:15:38.740
be a doer of the word.

00:15:38.740 --> 00:15:41.960
God wants us to respond properly to his word.

00:15:41.960 --> 00:15:44.540
Then there's a second aspect of this passage

00:15:44.540 --> 00:15:47.940
that we're gonna look at in verses 23 through 25,

00:15:47.940 --> 00:15:49.460
where we not only see the instruction,

00:15:49.460 --> 00:15:52.779
be a doer of the word and not a hearer only.

00:15:52.779 --> 00:15:55.140
And then he goes into this illustration

00:15:55.140 --> 00:15:57.260
in verses 23 through 25.

00:15:57.260 --> 00:15:59.559
Now we read down through this illustration.

00:15:59.559 --> 00:16:02.300
We won't take the time to read this passage again,

00:16:02.300 --> 00:16:04.100
but as he gives us this illustration,

00:16:04.100 --> 00:16:06.300
basically James says this, James says,

00:16:06.300 --> 00:16:08.839
I'm gonna present to you two different people.

00:16:08.839 --> 00:16:11.520
Let's talk about exhibit A.

00:16:11.520 --> 00:16:14.700
Exhibit A is the person who comes before the mirror

00:16:14.700 --> 00:16:17.380
and we're just going to simply identify this person

00:16:17.380 --> 00:16:19.179
as the looker.

00:16:19.179 --> 00:16:20.339
This is the person who,

00:16:20.339 --> 00:16:22.460
when they come before the mirror of God's word,

00:16:22.460 --> 00:16:25.520
they're willing to look into the mirror,

00:16:25.520 --> 00:16:28.860
see what God's word says, even hear it,

00:16:28.860 --> 00:16:33.860
but then they go away and they forget what God's word says.

00:16:34.040 --> 00:16:37.100
There's an interesting word in verse 22

00:16:37.100 --> 00:16:39.300
and it's the verse 23, excuse me.

00:16:39.300 --> 00:16:43.480
It says this, beholding his natural face in a glass.

00:16:43.480 --> 00:16:45.080
The word beholding there is this,

00:16:45.080 --> 00:16:49.559
it means to perceive clearly, to understand.

00:16:49.559 --> 00:16:51.640
In other words, this person is presented

00:16:51.640 --> 00:16:53.000
with the truth of God's word,

00:16:53.000 --> 00:16:54.880
whether it's in reading God's word,

00:16:54.880 --> 00:16:56.240
hearing God's word preached,

00:16:56.240 --> 00:16:57.839
it could be done through godly music

00:16:57.839 --> 00:16:59.860
that conveys the truth of God's word,

00:16:59.860 --> 00:17:01.720
but somehow they hear God's word

00:17:01.720 --> 00:17:03.760
and it isn't that they don't understand it.

00:17:03.760 --> 00:17:07.619
It isn't that it's too high for them to understand.

00:17:07.619 --> 00:17:09.240
God's word has been made clear.

00:17:10.179 --> 00:17:11.000
It's been explained to them.

00:17:11.000 --> 00:17:13.880
It's been made evident to them what needs to happen,

00:17:13.880 --> 00:17:18.380
but they are just willing to look.

00:17:18.380 --> 00:17:21.059
And then they purposefully go away

00:17:21.059 --> 00:17:25.020
and they forget what manner of man they were.

00:17:25.020 --> 00:17:27.339
The word forget there is the idea of neglect.

00:17:27.339 --> 00:17:30.020
You ever forgotten something, forgotten keys?

00:17:30.020 --> 00:17:33.260
Maybe you've forgotten your wallet or your purse somewhere.

00:17:33.260 --> 00:17:34.779
Maybe you've forgotten something

00:17:34.779 --> 00:17:36.220
even more important than that.

00:17:36.220 --> 00:17:38.380
Maybe you've forgotten your child somewhere.

00:17:39.420 --> 00:17:42.059
And you know, when something is important to you,

00:17:42.059 --> 00:17:44.619
you try not to forget it, right?

00:17:45.540 --> 00:17:48.140
Well, here he says for the looker,

00:17:48.140 --> 00:17:50.420
the things that he's learned, read,

00:17:50.420 --> 00:17:52.500
heard from God's word and knows he ought to put

00:17:52.500 --> 00:17:54.540
into practice in his life,

00:17:54.540 --> 00:17:57.179
the one who is the looker, exhibit A,

00:17:57.179 --> 00:17:59.700
the one who ultimately when the storms arise,

00:17:59.700 --> 00:18:02.860
the floods come, their life is gonna be a disaster,

00:18:02.860 --> 00:18:06.580
they neglect, they forget.

00:18:06.580 --> 00:18:09.440
They make really a choice

00:18:09.440 --> 00:18:11.679
not to apply God's word to their life.

00:18:11.679 --> 00:18:12.520
Why?

00:18:12.520 --> 00:18:13.920
Because they're just simply a looker.

00:18:13.920 --> 00:18:16.080
They're even willing to look into God's word

00:18:16.080 --> 00:18:18.240
and find information to help other people.

00:18:18.240 --> 00:18:20.160
They're willing to look into God's word

00:18:20.160 --> 00:18:23.399
to hopefully find some sort of a life vest

00:18:23.399 --> 00:18:24.899
that when trouble comes into their life,

00:18:24.899 --> 00:18:26.520
they can maybe use God's word that way.

00:18:26.520 --> 00:18:29.640
But to allow God's word to affect their daily life,

00:18:29.640 --> 00:18:34.640
they're just a looker and not choosing to be a doer.

00:18:35.100 --> 00:18:36.820
That's exhibit A.

00:18:36.820 --> 00:18:40.140
Exhibit B, as we continue to go on in these verses then,

00:18:40.140 --> 00:18:43.260
we see that there is something that is different.

00:18:43.260 --> 00:18:48.260
We don't see this one who is exhibit A

00:18:48.580 --> 00:18:50.440
not being exposed to God's word.

00:18:50.440 --> 00:18:51.619
They've heard God's word.

00:18:51.619 --> 00:18:53.080
They've heard truth presented.

00:18:53.080 --> 00:18:54.840
That's not what really makes the difference.

00:18:54.840 --> 00:18:58.340
The difference is exhibit B is someone

00:18:58.340 --> 00:19:00.299
who hears the word of God,

00:19:00.299 --> 00:19:02.859
comes before the mirror of God's word

00:19:02.859 --> 00:19:04.400
and their choice is this.

00:19:05.160 --> 00:19:06.380
I don't wanna neglect this.

00:19:06.380 --> 00:19:09.739
I don't want this to just come in one ear and out the other.

00:19:09.739 --> 00:19:12.179
I want to have God's blessing on my life.

00:19:12.179 --> 00:19:15.220
So I'm going to choose to be a hearer of the word

00:19:15.220 --> 00:19:19.100
and a doer of the word.

00:19:19.100 --> 00:19:21.619
If we look at these two different people,

00:19:21.619 --> 00:19:23.979
we classified exhibit A as the looker.

00:19:23.979 --> 00:19:26.380
Exhibit B this morning,

00:19:26.380 --> 00:19:28.820
I would classify him as this kind of a person.

00:19:28.820 --> 00:19:31.020
He is a lingerer.

00:19:31.020 --> 00:19:32.100
He is a lingerer.

00:19:32.100 --> 00:19:34.200
Notice the word as we read down

00:19:34.200 --> 00:19:37.200
through this passage of scripture in verse 25,

00:19:37.200 --> 00:19:39.960
it says, but who so looketh into the perfect law of liberty

00:19:39.960 --> 00:19:43.440
and continueth therein.

00:19:43.440 --> 00:19:46.960
My mind goes to that person who is lingering,

00:19:46.960 --> 00:19:49.359
who is continuing,

00:19:49.359 --> 00:19:51.400
who is seeking to stay with

00:19:51.400 --> 00:19:54.919
or stand near something as long as they can.

00:19:55.880 --> 00:19:59.960
And if they can't stay by that any longer,

00:19:59.960 --> 00:20:00.799
then they can't.

00:20:00.799 --> 00:20:03.799
They carry the thought, they carry the concept,

00:20:03.799 --> 00:20:06.079
they carry the memory in their mind,

00:20:06.079 --> 00:20:07.999
they take it with them.

00:20:09.939 --> 00:20:12.719
I mentioned that half of our family

00:20:12.719 --> 00:20:14.879
is not with us this morning.

00:20:14.879 --> 00:20:17.379
But you know, there are different ways

00:20:17.379 --> 00:20:20.019
that we can stay in touch.

00:20:20.019 --> 00:20:22.019
There are different ways that we can think

00:20:22.019 --> 00:20:24.659
about our children, and even though we may be

00:20:24.659 --> 00:20:27.219
hundreds of miles apart,

00:20:27.219 --> 00:20:29.199
we can still have the thought of them.

00:20:29.199 --> 00:20:30.899
It's not like they're completely gone,

00:20:30.899 --> 00:20:32.499
that they've disappeared, that we don't want

00:20:32.499 --> 00:20:33.799
anything to do with them.

00:20:33.799 --> 00:20:35.499
You wanna know something, we go around the campsite

00:20:35.499 --> 00:20:37.199
and there are memories that begin to flash

00:20:37.199 --> 00:20:39.139
into our minds all of the time,

00:20:39.139 --> 00:20:40.779
of the things that our children have done

00:20:40.779 --> 00:20:42.279
as they've grown up there at camp,

00:20:42.279 --> 00:20:43.939
and we see them there, why?

00:20:43.939 --> 00:20:47.279
Because the memory, the importance,

00:20:47.279 --> 00:20:51.459
it's significant to us, and it lingers in our mind.

00:20:53.859 --> 00:20:56.399
Hey, can I ask you this question this morning?

00:20:56.419 --> 00:20:59.359
What is your habit when you hear God's word?

00:20:59.359 --> 00:21:01.359
Do you come into God's word and you walk out

00:21:01.359 --> 00:21:06.179
these doors and God's word is forgotten?

00:21:06.179 --> 00:21:08.639
Kelly will often encourage the young people

00:21:08.639 --> 00:21:10.479
before they leave to not let the gates

00:21:10.479 --> 00:21:13.279
at the end of the road as they go out,

00:21:13.279 --> 00:21:15.939
which is actually the entrance when they come in, okay,

00:21:15.939 --> 00:21:18.479
that when they go out the front gate,

00:21:18.479 --> 00:21:20.719
to don't let them be like giant erasers

00:21:20.719 --> 00:21:22.479
where everything that they've heard at camp this week

00:21:22.479 --> 00:21:24.319
from God's word and they learn in their devotions

00:21:24.319 --> 00:21:25.959
from their counselors, from the preaching,

00:21:26.779 --> 00:21:28.759
from the instruction, don't let it be like a magic eraser

00:21:28.759 --> 00:21:30.779
that all of a sudden when you go out that gate,

00:21:30.779 --> 00:21:32.259
that whew, it's gone.

00:21:33.619 --> 00:21:35.559
Take the truth with you.

00:21:36.699 --> 00:21:40.299
Are these doors like mental erasers,

00:21:40.299 --> 00:21:41.859
spiritual erasers to you?

00:21:42.799 --> 00:21:46.339
I've heard God's word, now I've gotta get back to life,

00:21:46.339 --> 00:21:48.639
and you don't take God's word with you?

00:21:48.639 --> 00:21:52.279
Or do you allow God's word to linger in your heart?

00:21:52.279 --> 00:21:53.579
Can I give you a food illustration?

00:21:53.579 --> 00:21:55.079
It's the idea of a marinade.

00:21:55.979 --> 00:21:57.379
What do you do with a marinade?

00:21:57.379 --> 00:21:59.759
You don't just pop it into a bag for five seconds,

00:21:59.759 --> 00:22:01.159
take it back out, right?

00:22:01.159 --> 00:22:04.219
If you really want that flavor to get into the meat,

00:22:04.219 --> 00:22:06.259
you have to let it sit in there for a while

00:22:06.259 --> 00:22:09.699
so that it begins to soak it up, it begins to permeate it.

00:22:11.339 --> 00:22:13.499
Do you let God's word linger in your heart?

00:22:14.899 --> 00:22:16.339
Do you let God's word begin to get in

00:22:16.339 --> 00:22:18.879
and permeate your life, or do we respond

00:22:18.879 --> 00:22:23.179
like the wicked witch in the Grimm's fairy tales

00:22:23.179 --> 00:22:25.519
that when it tells us something we don't like to hear,

00:22:26.379 --> 00:22:28.739
automatically we get shut off to God's word?

00:22:28.739 --> 00:22:30.979
God, you can't penetrate that area of my life.

00:22:30.979 --> 00:22:34.919
No, sir, you can't tell me how to thank God.

00:22:34.919 --> 00:22:36.419
Say, does God really tell me how to thank?

00:22:36.419 --> 00:22:38.679
Read Philippians chapter four in verse eight.

00:22:38.679 --> 00:22:40.819
Whatsoever things are true, honest, just, pure, lovely,

00:22:40.819 --> 00:22:42.119
if there's virtue, if there's any praise,

00:22:42.119 --> 00:22:43.919
think on these things, God says.

00:22:43.919 --> 00:22:46.299
Here's what you ought to be thinking.

00:22:46.299 --> 00:22:48.599
So God's word addresses the areas of our lives,

00:22:48.599 --> 00:22:51.599
and God applies his truth to different areas of our lives.

00:22:51.599 --> 00:22:53.799
When he shows areas of our lives

00:22:53.859 --> 00:22:54.779
that are in the mirror of God's word

00:22:54.779 --> 00:22:57.319
that we need to change, do we get mad at the mirror

00:22:57.319 --> 00:23:00.199
and we go away, being someone who is just a looker,

00:23:00.199 --> 00:23:02.159
or are we someone who is willing to linger

00:23:02.159 --> 00:23:06.039
and let God's word permeate, affect, and change our lives?

00:23:06.959 --> 00:23:08.699
So we see in this passage of scripture

00:23:08.699 --> 00:23:11.199
that God's word gives to us the instruction.

00:23:11.199 --> 00:23:14.539
The instruction is this, be a doer of the word,

00:23:14.539 --> 00:23:16.079
not just a hearer.

00:23:16.079 --> 00:23:18.039
The illustration that he gives to us

00:23:18.039 --> 00:23:20.919
is that of someone who comes before the mirror.

00:23:20.919 --> 00:23:22.279
The looker is the one who says,

00:23:22.299 --> 00:23:24.359
I'll look into God's word, I don't like it,

00:23:24.359 --> 00:23:26.359
I'm gonna neglect it, I'll forget it,

00:23:26.359 --> 00:23:28.559
I'll hear it, but that's about it.

00:23:28.559 --> 00:23:30.279
And then exhibit B is the one who says,

00:23:30.279 --> 00:23:33.039
I wanna be a doer of the word.

00:23:33.039 --> 00:23:36.239
You say, why is it so important to be a doer of the word?

00:23:36.239 --> 00:23:39.479
Well, you may have noticed when we went to verse 22

00:23:39.479 --> 00:23:42.999
that I didn't read the final phrase.

00:23:42.999 --> 00:23:46.439
The final part of verse 22 says this,

00:23:46.439 --> 00:23:48.679
first part says, but be ye doers of the word

00:23:48.679 --> 00:23:50.059
and not hearers only.

00:23:50.059 --> 00:23:55.059
Notice these last four words, deceiving your own selves.

00:23:56.499 --> 00:23:58.019
The last thing that I want us to notice

00:23:58.019 --> 00:24:00.259
in this passage of scripture is James,

00:24:00.259 --> 00:24:02.419
God really through James as he's writing,

00:24:02.419 --> 00:24:07.419
shares with us what I call the illusion, the illusion.

00:24:08.459 --> 00:24:12.419
You ever seen somebody do some sort of an illusion?

00:24:12.419 --> 00:24:16.099
Might be a clown pulling a scarf out of a fake thumb,

00:24:16.099 --> 00:24:19.019
so hopefully I didn't ruin that for anybody.

00:24:19.019 --> 00:24:21.699
Maybe you've seen a magician do some sort of a magic trick

00:24:21.699 --> 00:24:23.779
and you're trying to think, ooh, that's sleight of hand,

00:24:23.779 --> 00:24:24.619
how did he do that?

00:24:24.619 --> 00:24:25.500
I don't understand.

00:24:25.500 --> 00:24:29.359
And there is this illusion that is there.

00:24:31.239 --> 00:24:33.299
Sometimes the hardest thing for us to be willing

00:24:33.299 --> 00:24:35.940
to accept from God's word is this,

00:24:35.940 --> 00:24:38.419
you're deceiving yourself.

00:24:38.419 --> 00:24:41.579
You're living an illusion.

00:24:41.579 --> 00:24:44.299
The word deceive as we see it here is that,

00:24:44.299 --> 00:24:49.299
it's the idea of someone who is miscalculating something,

00:24:49.299 --> 00:24:51.299
mis-evaluating.

00:24:52.419 --> 00:24:54.779
And so it's somebody who says, I'm gonna go to the store

00:24:54.779 --> 00:24:57.459
and I'm gonna buy this, I have $20, but it's $50

00:24:57.459 --> 00:24:59.179
and they still think that they should be able to get it.

00:24:59.179 --> 00:25:02.779
You're mis-calculating.

00:25:02.779 --> 00:25:04.979
You're not evaluating it properly

00:25:04.979 --> 00:25:09.099
and so James puts in here this warning to his readers

00:25:09.099 --> 00:25:13.720
